{"word":"ἀκραιφνής","slug":"ἀκραιφνής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀκραιφνής</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:syncopated'>syncop.</a> form of <el>ἀκεραιοφανής</el> (<el>ἀκέραιος, φαίνομαι</el>)\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>unmixed, pure</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>πενία ἀκρ.</el> <i>utter</i> poverty, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>unharmed, entire</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>integer</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>untouched by</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}